  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="sonnet">
   <l>GIue pardon (blessed Soule) to my bold cryes</l>
   <l>If they (importund) interrupt thy song,</l>
   <l>Which nowe with ioyfull notes thou sing'st, among</l>
   <l>The Angel-Quiristers of heau'nly skyes:</l>
   <l>Giue pardon eake (sweet Soule) to my flow cries,</l>
   <l>That since I saw thee now it is so long,</l>
   <l>And yet the teares that vnto thee belong,</l>
   <l>To thee as yet they did not sacrifice:</l>
   <l>I did not know that thou wert dead before,</l>
   <l>I did not feele the griefe I did susteine,</l>
   <l>"The greater stroke astonisheth the more,</l>
   <l>"Astonishment takes from vs sence of paine,</l>
   <l>I stood amaz'd when others teares begun,</l>
   <l>And now begin to weepe, when they haue doone.</l>
</div>
